[0m[49m[38;5;9m-  90     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m ### HIGH-3: No data minimization guidance for the recommendation delivery layer
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Finding:** The Prerequisites table states "all API calls over TLS" but does not specify TLS version. AWS services support TLS 1.2 as the minimum for most endpoints, but some older SDK versions or client configurations may negotiate TLS 1.0/1.1. For HIPAA compliance, TLS 1.2 should be the explicit minimum.
