[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 152     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m ## Strengths
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Specific Praise
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### ✅ Problem Framing Is Exceptional
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening scenario (care manager, 200 patients, 8 call slots, "the question isn't who to call, it's when") is one of the best problem framings in the entire cookbook. It makes the timing problem viscerally clear to a non-technical reader in three paragraphs. The $15,000 hospitalization vs. $50 wasted call framing gives executives the ROI hook they need.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### ✅ Survival Analysis Explanation Is Accessible and Accurate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The progression from "risk as a point" to "risk as a trajectory" to "hazard functions" to "dynamic survival models" is pedagogically excellent. A reader with no statistics background can follow the logic. A reader with statistics training will find the technical claims accurate. This is hard to achieve and the recipe does it well.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### ✅ Honest Take Is Genuinely Honest
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The admission that "most organizations that attempt optimal timing prediction end up building a really good risk score and calling it a timing model" is exactly the kind of practitioner wisdom that makes this cookbook valuable. The intervention fatigue discussion and the self-fulfilling prophecy problem are real issues that most ML papers ignore. Calling them out explicitly, with practical implications, is excellent.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### ✅ Hybrid Recommendation Is Pragmatic
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The explicit recommendation to start with "dynamic survival model + simple decision rules" rather than jumping to full causal/RL is the right advice for 95% of healthcare organizations. The recipe correctly identifies that the infrastructure for the simple version is the same infrastructure the complex version needs, which gives teams a migration path without over-engineering upfront.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### ✅ Pseudocode Is Accessible to Non-Coders
[0m[49m[39m  153, 290[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 154     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Exceptional problem framing.** The opening scenario (care manager with 200 patients, 8 call slots) immediately grounds the technical content in clinical reality. This is the best problem statement in Chapter 7.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 155     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Honest complexity acknowledgment.** The recipe correctly positions this as research/pilot, doesn't oversell causal inference capabilities, and recommends starting with the hybrid approach.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 156     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Self-fulfilling prophecy discussion.** Calling out how successful intervention erodes training signal is a sophisticated insight that most healthcare ML content ignores.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 157     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Intervention fatigue modeling.** Including dampening factors for recent contact and declined outreach shows real-world operational awareness.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 158     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Architecture matches the problem.** The split between batch (model training, daily features) and real-time (event-driven scoring) paths is appropriate for the latency requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 159     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **The "Honest Take" section is genuinely honest.** It doesn't hedge with corporate language; it tells the reader what will actually happen when they try to build this.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The step-by-step walkthrough with business-level explanations ("what goes wrong if you skip it") before each pseudocode block makes the recipe accessible to the stated mixed audience. The comments within pseudocode are generous without being condescending.
